1: AguilaTrades, a giant whale, closed its long position of BTC worth $434 million with 20x leverage, with a loss of $12.48 million;
2: Kyoyo, a giant whale, shorted BTC with 40x leverage, with a floating profit of $5.17 million;
3: Tencent has not considered acquiring Nexon, the developer of "DNF" and "MapleStory";
4: Walmart and Amazon are planning to issue their own stablecoins;
5: Long-term Bitcoin holders have increased their holdings by more than 880,000 BTC in the past 30 days;
6: Viewpoint: The latest conflict between Israel and Iran is only short-term noise, and the time to buy the bottom should be grasped in a timely and cautious manner;
7: Iranian government: The attack would not have happened without the coordination and permission of the United States;
8: Israel will close its embassies and consulates worldwide;
9: Iranian President: Iran's reasonable and forceful response will make Israel regret its stupid behavior;
10: Coinbase: It is expected that the upward trend of BTC will continue in the second half of the year, with economic growth, corporate adoption and regulatory clarity as the main driving forces;
11: CryptoQuant analyst: Bitcoin The 102000-105000 range may become a new support. If it falls below $100,000, the selling pressure may increase;
12: Users with 240 Binance Alpha points can participate in the SGC TGE event, which will consume 15 points;
13: The whale transferred 609 billion PEPE to Binance an hour ago, about $6.43 million;
14: Allianz: Postponed the Fed's interest rate cut expectations from October to December;
15: Smarter Web Company, a British listed company, increased its holdings of 74.27 BTC, with a total holding of 242.34 BTC;
16: The US court imposed a $25 million fine and compensation on the parties involved in the My Big Coin fraud case;
17: Believe founder: The new anti-sniping mechanism is now online, and the structure and mechanism of LAUNCHCOIN are being studied.
